<paragraph blockId="11.[443,805,930,986]" box="[478,769,962,986]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1410">
(
<figureCitation box="[486,637,962,986]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="4.[212,279,1585,1607]" captionTargetBox="[238,1143,178,1555]" captionTargetId="figure-46@4.[238,1144,177,1556]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 1. Frons and palpus of male. (A, B) Pseudostegana acutifoliolata sp. nov.; (C,D) Pseudostegana bilobata sp. nov.; (E,F) Pseudostegana bipartita sp. nov.; (G,H) Pseudostegana minutipalpata sp. nov.; (I,J) Pseudostegana insularis sp. nov.; (K,L) Pseudostegana silvana sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5209711" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5209711/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="1410">Figures 1E,F</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation box="[649,684,962,986]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="6.[212,279,1137,1159]" captionTargetBox="[240,1144,176,1106]" captionTargetId="figure-263@6.[240,1145,175,1107]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 2. Wing of male: (A). Pseudostegana acutifoliolata sp. nov.; (B) Pseudostegana bilobata sp. nov.; (C) Pseudostegana bipartita sp. nov.; (D Pseudostegana minutipalpata sp. nov.; (E) Pseudostegana insularis sp. nov.; (F) Pseudostegana silvana sp. nov. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5209715" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5209715/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="1410">2C</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation box="[695,762,962,986]" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="12.[212,279,803,825]" captionTargetBox="[214,1168,172,773]" captionTargetId="figure-215@12.[213,1171,172,774]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figure 5. Pseudostegana bipartita sp. nov., male. (A) epandrium, cercus and surstylus; (B) cercus; (C,D) hypandrium, paramere, gonopods, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme. For orientations and organizations see Figure 3. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5209721" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5209721/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="1410">5Aâ€“E</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[144,253,1034,1058]" box="[144,253,1034,1058]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1410">
<emphasis box="[144,253,1034,1058]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="1410">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[144,1103,1074,1130]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1410">
Paramere distally deeply bifurcated, with one small projection in ventral view (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="12.[212,279,803,825]" captionTargetBox="[214,1168,172,773]" captionTargetId="figure-215@12.[213,1171,172,774]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figure 5. Pseudostegana bipartita sp. nov., male. (A) epandrium, cercus and surstylus; (B) cercus; (C,D) hypandrium, paramere, gonopods, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme. For orientations and organizations see Figure 3. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5209721" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5209721/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="1410">Figure 5C,D</figureCitation>
); aedeagus apically roundly expanded (
<figureCitation box="[652,800,1106,1130]" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="12.[212,279,803,825]" captionTargetBox="[214,1168,172,773]" captionTargetId="figure-215@12.[213,1171,172,774]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figure 5. Pseudostegana bipartita sp. nov., male. (A) epandrium, cercus and surstylus; (B) cercus; (C,D) hypandrium, paramere, gonopods, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme. For orientations and organizations see Figure 3. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5209721" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5209721/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="1410">Figure 5C,D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[144,272,1191,1215]" box="[144,272,1191,1215]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1410">
<emphasis box="[144,272,1191,1215]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="1410">Description</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[144,662,1231,1255]" box="[144,662,1231,1255]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1410">Only important characters are described here.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[144,1104,1303,1391]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1410">
<emphasis box="[144,212,1303,1327]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="1410">Head.</emphasis>
Ocellar triangle black on upper two-thirds, brown on lower one-third. Frons brownish yellow. Pedicel yellow; first flagellomere greyish black. Face mostly brown. Clypeus dark brown. Gena brown. Palpus brownish black, broad and large in male.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[144,1104,1439,1527]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1410">
<emphasis box="[144,234,1440,1464]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="1410">Thorax.</emphasis>
Scutum yellow to yellowish brown. Pleura dark brown to black, broadened in male, medially half as wide as long. Katepisternal setae two. Scutellum brownish yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[144,299,1573,1597]" box="[144,299,1573,1597]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1410">
<emphasis box="[144,204,1573,1597]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="1410">Legs.</emphasis>
Yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[144,1105,1645,1701]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1410">
<emphasis box="[144,249,1645,1669]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="1410">Abdomen</emphasis>
. Tergites glossy black, except for first and second orange yellow medially. Sternites, first and second yellow, but others dark brown.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5209721" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5209721" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5209721/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="1411" startId="12.[212,279,803,825]" targetBox="[214,1168,172,773]" targetPageId="12">
<paragraph blockId="12.[212,1172,803,884]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1411">
Figure 5. 
<taxonomicName authority="Li &amp; Gao &amp; Chen, 2010" authorityName="Li &amp; Gao &amp; Chen" authorityYear="2010" box="[316,555,804,826]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Pseudostegana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="1411" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bipartita" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[316,555,804,826]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1411">Pseudostegana bipartita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[561,644,804,825]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1411" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, male. (A) epandrium, cercus and surstylus; (B) cercus; (C,D) hypandrium, paramere, gonopods, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme. For orientations and organizations see Figure 3. Scale bars: 0.1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="12.[212,1172,933,1053]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1411">
<emphasis box="[212,404,933,957]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1411">Male terminalia.</emphasis>
Epandrium slightly roundly protruded on ventral margin, with about 11 setae (
<figureCitation box="[410,538,965,989]" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="12.[212,279,803,825]" captionTargetBox="[214,1168,172,773]" captionTargetId="figure-215@12.[213,1171,172,774]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figure 5. Pseudostegana bipartita sp. nov., male. (A) epandrium, cercus and surstylus; (B) cercus; (C,D) hypandrium, paramere, gonopods, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme. For orientations and organizations see Figure 3. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5209721" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5209721/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="1411">Figure 5A</figureCitation>
). Surstylus protruded on antero- and posteroventral corners, with two setae subbasally (
<figureCitation box="[646,774,997,1021]" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="12.[212,279,803,825]" captionTargetBox="[214,1168,172,773]" captionTargetId="figure-215@12.[213,1171,172,774]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figure 5. Pseudostegana bipartita sp. nov., male. (A) epandrium, cercus and surstylus; (B) cercus; (C,D) hypandrium, paramere, gonopods, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme. For orientations and organizations see Figure 3. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5209721" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5209721/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="1411">Figure 5A</figureCitation>
). Cercus ventrally round (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="12.[212,279,803,825]" captionTargetBox="[214,1168,172,773]" captionTargetId="figure-215@12.[213,1171,172,774]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figure 5. Pseudostegana bipartita sp. nov., male. (A) epandrium, cercus and surstylus; (B) cercus; (C,D) hypandrium, paramere, gonopods, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme. For orientations and organizations see Figure 3. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5209721" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5209721/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="1411">Figure 5A,B</figureCitation>
). Basal process of aedeagus slender, apically slightly bifurcated (
<figureCitation box="[1010,1156,1029,1053]" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="12.[212,279,803,825]" captionTargetBox="[214,1168,172,773]" captionTargetId="figure-215@12.[213,1171,172,774]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figure 5. Pseudostegana bipartita sp. nov., male. (A) epandrium, cercus and surstylus; (B) cercus; (C,D) hypandrium, paramere, gonopods, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme. For orientations and organizations see Figure 3. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5209721" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5209721/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="1411">Figure 5C,D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
